00:01:00.905 --> 00:01:07.445
which we add to the container to affect all child items as a group on the row axis.

00:01:07.445 --> 00:01:09.905
A lot of these will be familiar already,

00:01:09.905 --> 00:01:15.665
such as end to place the items at the end of the row and also start.

00:01:15.665 --> 00:01:18.230
Go over to the main section,

00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:21.990
which is a container for these grid items.

00:01:22.900 --> 00:01:24.965
Just here we can add,

00:01:24.965 --> 00:01:32.295
justify items and set them to the end, refresh.

00:01:32.295 --> 00:01:35.375
Now all items are pushed to the end of the row.

00:01:35.375 --> 00:01:40.290
We also have start and you can probably guess what this does too,

00:01:40.430 --> 00:01:43.520
this moves everything to the start.

00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:46.715
Remember the second item which is used here,

00:01:46.715 --> 00:01:50.130
if we scroll back down, has more text.

00:01:50.130 --> 00:01:52.890
Therefore it fills more the available space.

00:01:52.890 --> 00:01:57.375
We can reinstate this for all the items move the same.

00:01:57.375 --> 00:02:00.780
Let's rename this item two.

00:02:00.780 --> 00:02:04.305
There we go, all items are now equal.

00:02:04.305 --> 00:02:07.800
The default value for this is stretch,

00:02:07.800 --> 00:02:12.000
select replace, start with stretch.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.940
How much you get the same effect which you began with,

00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:17.565
we'll also have centered too.

00:02:17.565 --> 00:02:20.150
This will replace all the items in the center of

00:02:20.150 --> 00:02:25.235
the row with width being determined by the content inside.

00:02:25.235 --> 00:02:30.425
We also have the option of baseline too if we're aligning the text.

